1
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,280
Hurry, find a place to hide!

2
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,480
There's a cave ahead.

3
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,380
Overseas Chinese.

4
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,480
We're all overseas Chinese.

5
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,970
What a coincidence.

6
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:26,770
We ran into our own people here.

7
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:34,760
You're hurt.

8
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:35,120
I'm fine.

9
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,400
Come, get in quickly.

10
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,880
It's safe inside.

11
00:02:37,880 --> 00:02:39,610
It's a minor scratch. I'm fine.

12
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,320
These Japs,

13
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,520
bomb us day and night.

14
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,160
They're really ruthless.

15
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,560
Don't they ever get tired?

16
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,000
Plus this damn weather.

17
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,840
Isn't this their daily routine?

18
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:52,960
But

19
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,020
the supplies on the trucks...

20
00:02:59,280 --> 00:02:59,960
No.

21
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,640
We can't just sit here.

22
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,000
What are you doing?

23
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:03,600
Calm down.

24
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,130
Are you trying to get yourself killed?

25
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,960
But we can't just sit here forever, can we?

26
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,160
It's no use going out.

27
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:15,170
This road is already treacherous.

28
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:18,400
They know we travel this road day and night.

29
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:20,840
If we don't turn on our headlights,

30
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,240
it's like driving blind.

31
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,200
But if we do,

32
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,600
we become sitting ducks.

33
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:27,040
They're trying to drive us to a dead end.

34
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,120
Brother.

35
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,760
Oh, no,

36
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:35,680
older brother.

37
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,920
Looking at you,

38
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:38,180
are you a mechanic too?

39
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,000
An overseas Chinese mechanic from Nanyang.

40
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,120
But looking at your age...

41
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,000
Exactly this year...

42
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:46,560
You're fifty?

43
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,130
I thought the recruitment age for mechanics was 20 to 40?

44
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:53,640
When I saw the call to return and support the country,

45
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:54,720
I was already 47.

46
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,770
Hard to believe, right?

47
00:03:58,079 --> 00:04:00,040
I lied about my age.

48
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,720
I was 17.

49
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:03,880
I even

50
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:05,400
changed my name.

51
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:06,720
Lying about your age is one thing,

52
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,840
but changing your name?

53
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:08,440
Yeah.

54
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:11,170
If I only changed my age and not my name,

55
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,160
and someone saw me out there,

56
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:16,160
wouldn't my relatives and friends still recognize me?

57
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:17,160
I see.

58
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:18,920
So you two...

59
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:21,440
One reported older, one reported younger.

60
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:24,200
Lied about your ages and even changed your names.

61
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,600
This level of deception,

62
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:26,620
I'm impressed.

63
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,140
You really went to great lengths.

64
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:32,440
When I tried to return, I was over the age limit.

65
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:36,300
I applied several times but was rejected for being too old.

66
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:40,760
Back then, my friends laughed at me.

67
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:43,320
Asking why I'd go back at this age,

68
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:46,140
saying I couldn't even lift an artillery shell.

69
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:49,120
I couldn't be bothered with them.

70
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:51,120
Then how did you manage to come back?

71
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:53,520
I wrote directly to Tan Kah Kee,

72
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:55,240
to show my determination to return.

73
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:55,960
And then?

74
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:00,000
Tan Kah Kee wrote to the Southwest Transport Team, saying:

75
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,200
'This passionate man has extensive knowledge of machinery and motors.

76
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,840
He is highly experienced.

77
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:06,080
Such dedication

78
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,040
is truly rare.'

79
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:11,200
He asked the transport team to make an exception and admit me.

80
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,800
So you were an exception.

81
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:14,840
And you?

82
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,800
As for me,

83
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:19,160
I was already this tall at 17.

84
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,600
Three years doesn't make much difference,

85
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,040
so I just put down 20.

86
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:22,960
Okay.

87
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:24,760
And I changed my name too.

88
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:28,240
You two make quite a pair.

89
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,940
Which transportation team are you from?

90
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:35,560
The Southwest Transportation Team.

91
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,690
The 80th Vanguard returning to China.

92
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:38,880
The 80th Vanguard.

93
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,340
You are the 80th Vanguard?

94
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:41,920
Of course.

95
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,050
We grew up together.

96
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,480
We even signed up together.

97
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,680
You grew up together.

98
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,480
Run!

99
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,000
Get ready to move. Hurry!

100
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:58,640
Watch out!

101
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:01,760
Let's go.

102
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:11,600
Come on.

103
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,800
Brother,

104
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,040
you have to hold on.

105
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,840
We will take you back.

106
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:22,980
I don't think I can make it.

107
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:24,680
Nonsense.

108
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,860
Didn't you say you'd take me back?

109
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,720
You can't leave me alone.

110
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,040
Wuyi,

111
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,360
I guess this time,

112
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,700
I'll have to break my promise.

113
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:51,440
I went to Nanyang with my parents when I was young.

114
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,770
I never expected...

115
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:57,640
When I heard about the Marco Polo Bridge Incident,

116
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:00,200
my heart...

117
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:06,800
As long as the invaders aren't driven out,

118
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:10,960
our people will never know peace.

119
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,840
When I returned to China,

120
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,000
they asked me,

121
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,960
was I afraid?

122
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:21,920
Was it worth it?

123
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:25,480
Leaving your wife and children behind,

124
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,680
was it hard?

125
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:31,480
This is my root.

126
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:34,240
If the root is gone,

127
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:37,040
the leaves will wither.

128
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:44,200
These Japanese

129
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,960
want to uproot us entirely.

130
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,520
Brother,

131
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:50,560
you will definitely make it back,

132
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,400
and tell them

133
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,320
we are not cowards.

134
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:57,159
Uproot us?

135
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:59,480
It's not that easy.

136
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:03,400
The soldiers fighting to the death on the front lines.

137
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,600
At least,

138
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:08,490
they have to ask if we Nanyang overseas Chinese agree first.

139
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:10,240
At least,

140
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:12,960
they have to get past me first.

141
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:13,760
Right.

142
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,970
Even though they bomb us every day,

143
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,760
they can't figure out

144
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:20,320
why this road can never be destroyed.

145
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:24,340
This is the meaning of our return.

146
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,240
That's right.

147
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,880
My brother returned to China a year ago,

148
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,720
and there's still no news of him.

149
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,679
Some say he's dead.

150
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:36,360
Others say he became a deserter.

151
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,780
I don't believe it.

152
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,640
At least,

153
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:41,770
at least he told me before he returned,

154
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:46,200
I'll save the country, you support the family.

155
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,720
Those who say your brother is a deserter

156
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:54,480
are talking absolute nonsense.

157
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,720
Everyone who came back

158
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:58,400
brought the determination to die for our country.

159
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,720
Either we live, or we die.

160
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:03,120
Where are these deserters from?

161
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:06,360
Yes.

162
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,720
Chen Jiageng said,

163
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:11,840
we are overseas Chinese.

164
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,680
Though we live abroad,

165
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:18,000
our hearts are with our motherland.

166
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:23,320
We represent millions of overseas Chinese returning to serve.

167
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:25,440
None of us are cowards.

168
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:31,040
We cannot let down the expectations of every overseas Chinese.

169
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,560
We share the same destiny.

170
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,000
Xiaowu.

171
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,280
I want to hear

172
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:47,000
you play the harmonica again.

173
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:22,080
Brother.

174
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:23,760
Brother.

175
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,800
Brother.

176
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:48,410
Brother.

177
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:51,160
Wake up, brother.

178
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:17,240
Watch out.
